timeline.bodyText:
This doesn't work as it should. In an Iterator, when you invoke next, you get the "next" result and on a subsequent invocation, you should get the following item.
Your implementation does not do this. Actually it seems to to advance the "next" every time you invoke hasNext ... so if you do:
i.hasNext();
i.hasNext();

then your iterator has advanced two positions. hasNext should be a side-effect-free operation.

